Canonical **agent** contracts live in `{{AGENTS_CANONICAL_DIR}}`; their
harness-specific files (`.claude/agents/`, `.claude/commands/<agent>.md`) are thin
pointers. The two **orchestration commands** (`pipeline-orchestrator`, `dispatch`)
are the exception: they are commands, not agents — their canonical body lives
directly in `.claude/commands/`.

## Orchestration matrix (intent → owner)

One owning asset per intent. Never fork the workflow: do not run a parallel
flow for the same task; pick the owner and cite anything else as reference.

| Trigger / intent | Owning asset | Human gate / escalation notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Route an ambiguous request to its owner | `{{AGENTS_CANONICAL_DIR}}dispatcher.md` | Read-only; outputs the owner path only. |
| Review staged changes before commit | `{{AGENTS_CANONICAL_DIR}}blind-code-reviewer.md` | Mandatory before every commit (pre-commit review gate); blocks on non-empty `## Blocking`. |
| Security posture / secrets / auth surfaces | `{{AGENTS_CANONICAL_DIR}}security-reviewer.md` | Must report `PASS` before merge; findings route per escalation-policy. |
| Grade governance/instruction files | `{{AGENTS_CANONICAL_DIR}}instruction-auditor.md` | Scores below {{SCORE_THRESHOLD}} block the graded agent's spawn. |
| MR/PR merge readiness | `{{AGENTS_CANONICAL_DIR}}pr-pipeline-gate.md` | Read-only; merging itself follows the autonomy matrix in `.agentic/guides/policy/ai-policy.md`. |
| Staged multi-agent feature flow | `.claude/commands/pipeline-orchestrator.md` | Judgment gates via decision-router; `escalate_on` flags stop the pipeline. |
| One-step-at-a-time routing (strict HITL) | `.claude/commands/dispatch.md` | Each step user-invoked; agents never chain autonomously. |
| Draft test cases from a story/bug (QA preset) | `{{AGENTS_CANONICAL_DIR}}test-case-generator.md` | Draft-only; upload to {{TICKET_ADAPTER}} is human-approved. |
| Automate approved test-case IDs (QA preset) | `{{AGENTS_CANONICAL_DIR}}test-automation-author.md` | Real-ID gate + existing-coverage gate; test execution per autonomy matrix. |
| Sync automation ↔ ticket steps after maintenance (QA preset) | `{{AGENTS_CANONICAL_DIR}}test-case-syncer.md` | Every {{TICKET_ADAPTER}} step update is a per-case human-approved write. |
| Triage a red/flaky test (QA preset) | `{{AGENTS_CANONICAL_DIR}}test-failure-triage.md` | Read-only; fixes follow `.agentic/guides/standards/flaky-protocol.md`. |
| Create tickets/bugs in {{TICKET_ADAPTER}} (QA preset) | `{{AGENTS_CANONICAL_DIR}}work-item-creator.md` | Every external write listed and human-confirmed before execution. |
